      "rationale": "Blood viscosity data sourced from a limited donor cohort (n=12), yielding ±18% uncertainty in apparent viscosity at 37°C. This limitation is explicitly documented and honestly reported. Sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) confirms viscosity is the dominant uncertainty source (S1=0.68), contributing to wide UQ bounds (±0.22 on RH index). Despite this, all predictions remain below RH=1 acceptance threshold even at the 97.5th percentile of the viscosity distribution. The gap is accepted as residual risk with documented justification. Geometric inputs from CMM measurements with ±0.02 mm accuracy; boundary conditions from calibrated flow meters ±1.5%. Overall model input characterization meets MRL 2 requirements given the honest documentation and threshold margin.",
